{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":82091,"duration_api_ms":70220,"num_turns":8,"result":"All checks pass. Here is the ExecutionPayload:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"change_summary\": \"Three amendments addressed: (1) Changed tracing::warn to tracing::error in unique_terminal_replay_match contract violation path (fs.rs:2839) so the invariant violation is logged at error level rather than being masked as a routine warning — callers still see 'no matching task run' but operators now see an error-level log identifying the contract violation. (2) Added deliberate-deviation documentation to safe_plan_hash_backfill None-provenance branch (fs.rs:2609-2621) and the running_entry_created_before_plan_is_not_backfilled_on_revisit test (service.rs:5274-5285), explicitly referencing Issue 3 acceptance criteria and explaining why None-provenance entries are intentionally not backfilled due to ambiguity between 'created before any plan' and 'legacy code version'. (3) Removed new-row auto-population of plan_hash from snapshot (fs.rs:3050) — effective_plan_hash now uses only plan_hash.map(str::to_owned), preventing the dispatch-v1/snapshot-v2 race from stamping entries with the wrong plan version. snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation still records the snapshot hash for provenance. Added dispatch_v1_snapshot_v2_race_does_not_conflict regression test. Updated 4 existing tests (plan_hash_auto_populated_from_snapshot, terminal_replay_after_plan_evolution_succeeds, start_replay_after_plan_evolution_does_not_conflict, safe_backfill_fills_plan_hash_when_snapshot_unchanged) to expect plan_hash=None after start without explicit plan_hash.\",\n  \"outstanding_risks\": [\n    \"Callers that previously relied on auto-population now get plan_hash=None on new entries unless they supply it explicitly. safe_plan_hash_backfill at completion time fills it when the snapshot hasn't evolved, but entries completed after plan evolution with no explicit plan_hash will remain plan_hash=None.\",\n    \"Pre-existing formatting drift in tests/unit/agent_execution_test.rs is unrelated to these changes.\"\n  ],\n  \"steps\": [\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Amendment 1: Changed tracing::warn! to tracing::error! in unique_terminal_replay_match contract violation guard (fs.rs:2839) where requested_run_id is Some but requested_started_at is None, so the invariant violation is logged at error level in all build modes.\",\n      \"order\": 1,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Amendment 2: Added deliberate-deviation-from-Issue-3 documentation comment to safe_plan_hash_backfill None-provenance branch (fs.rs:2609-2621), explaining the ambiguity rationale for skipping legacy entries — None could mean 'created before any plan' or 'legacy code version that didn't record provenance', so backfilling would risk silently relabeling.\",\n      \"order\": 2,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Amendment 2: Added deliberate-deviation doc comment to running_entry_created_before_plan_is_not_backfilled_on_revisit test (service.rs:5274-5285), referencing Issue 3 criteria and the correctness-over-completeness decision so future reviewers don't re-open this as a regression.\",\n      \"order\": 3,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Amendment 3: Removed new-row auto-population — changed effective_plan_hash from plan_hash.map(str::to_owned).or_else(|| current_snapshot_hash.clone()) to plan_hash.map(str::to_owned) at fs.rs:3050. Updated comment block (fs.rs:3040-3048) to document the dispatch-v1/snapshot-v2 race rationale. Kept snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation recording for provenance.\",\n      \"order\": 4,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Amendment 3: Added dispatch_v1_snapshot_v2_race_does_not_conflict regression test (service.rs:5174) — persists plan v1, advances snapshot to v2, starts bead without plan_hash (gets None), completes with explicit hash_v1, verifies no conflicting plan_hash error and entry carries v1 hash.\",\n      \"order\": 5,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Updated plan_hash_auto_populated_from_snapshot test: post-start assertion changed from Some(expected_plan_hash) to None (no auto-population on new rows). Post-completion assertion expects safe_plan_hash_backfill to fill plan_hash since snapshot hasn't evolved.\",\n      \"order\": 6,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Updated terminal_replay_after_plan_evolution_succeeds test: post-start assertion changed from Some(hash_v1) to None. Completion now supplies explicit plan_hash=hash_v1 instead of relying on auto-population. Terminal replay after v2 evolution retains v1.\",\n      \"order\": 7,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Updated start_replay_after_plan_evolution_does_not_conflict test: removed hash_v1 extraction via .expect(), replaced with assert plan_hash=None after start and after replay. No conflict possible since both sides are None.\",\n      \"order\": 8,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Updated safe_backfill_fills_plan_hash_when_snapshot_unchanged test: post-start assertion changed from Some(expected_hash) to None. Provenance assertion unchanged. Second phase (bead-provenance with explicit provenance) still verifies safe_plan_hash_backfill fills at completion.\",\n      \"order\": 9,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Ran cargo test (359 passed, 0 failed — new dispatch_v1_snapshot_v2_race_does_not_conflict test included), cargo clippy -- -D warnings (clean), cargo fmt --check (clean). Full test suite: 683 unit passed, 0 failed.\",\n      \"order\": 10,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"validation_evidence\": [\n    \"cargo test: 359 lib tests passed, 0 failed; 683 total unit tests passed, 0